"review_level": "None",
"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:1.15.2\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">1.15.2</span> 标题：无花果饼（poultice, fig cake）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">经文出处</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：דְּבֵלָה, תְּאֵנָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：dveleth t’enim)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs20:7\">2KI 20:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa38:21\">ISA 38:21</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：μάλαγμα</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：malagma)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Wis16:12\">WIS 16:12</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>无花果饼是把干无花果压在一起成为块状。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>这种干无花果块可以直接吃（参<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">9.5 水果干压成的饼块 (blocks of pressed dried fruit)&lt;REALIA:9.5&gt;</a> ）。干果可以保存很长时间。人们偶尔也把无花果饼贴在皮肤的疖子或脓肿上面，以软化皮肤，达到治疗的目的。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻译</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>在希西家得医治的故事中（<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs20:7\">2KI 20:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa38:21\">ISA 38:21</a> ），目前并不确定当时人们如何使用无花果进行治疗。希伯来文短语<em>dveleth t’enim</em> 的译法有：“捣碎的无花果”（“mashed figs”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> ）、“压碎的无花果糊”（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"French Common Language Version (Bible en français courant)\">FRCL</abbr> ）、“无花果膏”（“fig-plaster”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised English Bible (1989)\">REB</abbr> ）和“无花果做成的糊”（“paste made of figs”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> ）。在无花果不为人所知的地方，翻译者可以说“名为无花果的水果”，或者用当地某种既可以吃，又可以入药的水果来翻译这个词。</p>\n<p>在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Wis16:12\">WIS 16:12</a> 中，希腊文<em>malagma</em> 是指一种软化皮肤伤口或疮的敷布。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 和<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Traduction Oecuménique de la Bible (French, 1975)\">TOB</abbr> 所用的“ointment”（“膏油”）一词有些不准确，而<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 所用“poultice”（“膏药”）的意思含糊不清。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New American Bible (1970)\">NAB</abbr> 译成“application”（“敷用药”），这是一个可资借鉴的翻译方式。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Italian Common Language Version\">ITCL</abbr> 的翻译是“绷带”。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
